r the cutlets to a plate. (Reserve the skillet.) Reduce the heat under the skillet to medium. ','2011-03-24 17:27:23.482928','2011-03-24 17:27:23.482928');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(5,3,NULL,'Add the remaining teaspoon oil and garlic to the same skillet; cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.','2011-03-24 17:27:23.483499','2011-03-24 17:27:23.483499');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(6,3,NULL,'Whisk together the broth, lemon juice and 1 teaspoon flour, and add to the pan.','2011-03-24 17:27:23.484058','2011-03-24 17:27:23.484058');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(7,3,NULL,'Simmer sauce until reduced and thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.','2011-03-24 17:27:23.484612','2011-03-24 17:27:23.484612');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(8,3,NULL,'Stir in the vinegar, parsley and capers.','2011-03-24 17:27:23.485171','2011-03-24 17:27:23.485171');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(9,3,NULL,'Swirl in the butter until sauce is shiny and slightly thickened. ','2011-03-24 17:27:23.485830','2011-03-24 17:27:23.485830');INSERT INTO "directions" VALUES(10,3,NULL,'Serve chicken with the sauce. Toss the arugula and freshly grated lemon zest with a light drizzle of olive oil; season to taste with salt and pepper, scatter over chicken. Serve with pasta or potatoes as desired. ','2011-03-24 17:27:23.486431','2011-03-24 17:27:23.486431');INSERT INTO "sqlite_sequence" VALUES('sessions',3);INSERT INTO "sqlite_sequence" VALUES('measurements',11);INSERT INTO "sqlite_sequence" VALUES('recipes',3);INSERT INTO "sqlite_sequence" VALUES('directions',10);INSERT INTO "sqlite_sequence" VALUES('ingredients',13);